#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:2
msgid "CSP"
msgstr "CSP"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:5
msgid "CSP是什么？"
msgstr "What Is CSP?"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:6
msgid ""
"Content Security Policy，简称 "
"CSP，译作内容安全策略。顾名思义，这个规范与内容安全有关，主要是用来定义哪些资源可以被当前页面加载，减少 XSS 的发生。"
msgstr ""
"Content Security Policy, abbreviated as CSP, is a specification related "
"to content security. It is mainly used to define which resources can be "
"loaded by the current page and to reduce XSS."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:9
msgid "配置"
msgstr "Configuration"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:10
msgid "CSP策略可以通过 HTTP 头信息或者 meta 元素定义。"
msgstr "A CSP policy can be defined through an HTTP header or a meta element."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:12
msgid "CSP 有三类："
msgstr "There are three CSP header variants:"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:14
msgid "Content-Security-Policy  (Google Chrome)"
msgstr "Content-Security-Policy  (Google Chrome)"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:15
msgid "X-Content-Security-Policy (Firefox)"
msgstr "X-Content-Security-Policy (Firefox)"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:16
msgid "X-WebKit-CSP (WebKit-based browsers, e.g. Safari)"
msgstr "X-WebKit-CSP (WebKit-based browsers, e.g. Safari)"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:25
msgid ""
"HTTP Content-Security-Policy 头可以指定一个或多个资源是安全的，而Content-Security-Policy-"
"Report-Only则是允许服务器检查（非强制）一个策略。多个头的策略定义由优先采用最先定义的。"
msgstr ""
"The HTTP Content-Security-Policy header can specify that one or more "
"resources are safe, while Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only allows the "
"server to check a policy without enforcing it. When multiple headers define "
"policies, the first defined policy takes precedence."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/csp.rst:27
msgid "HTML Meta : ::"
msgstr "HTML Meta: ::"

